article_title: Iran’s Nuclear Report Won’t Be ‘Black and White,’ U.N. Official Says
article_text:
The United Nations atomic energy arm is unlikely to draw clear conclusions in its report next month on whether Tehran once had a nuclear weapons program, the agency’s chief suggested on Thursday.

Failure to reach a final judgment on whether Iran was once seeking nuclear weapons know-how appears unlikely to scuttle the full implementation of July’s nuclear accord between Iran and six world powers. However, it could slow the process of...
